I took my @canmoresport watch ⌚️ out on the course for some fun and let me tell you, not only is it great for when I find myself in the wrong fairways, but it also keeps track of my daily activities. The Champions for Charity National Championship hosted by @lexususa is one of my favorite events of the year. 🗓️ This itinerary over the next few days consists of golf at Spyglass Hill, Spanish Bay, and Pebble Beach. . .some would probably say it’s the ultimate bucket list. 

Pairing great golf with philanthropy, the Champions for Charity program has raised over $500M throughout the country, supporting local tournaments by making a donation to each associated charity, while offering competitors the opportunity to win a Lexus! Can't come to Ireland without visiting a distillery, right? 🥃

During my time here, I had the incredible opportunity to explore @powerscourtdistilleryltd , the home of @fercullenwhiskey . It was a journey into the world of fine whiskey, where I discovered the proper way to taste and appreciate every sip, and let me tell you, it makes all the difference! 👅 

Did you know there's a proper way to taste whiskey? If not, don't worry, I just learned it myself and it's a game-changer. 

Let me walk you through it:

Step 1: Take a deep breath in.
Step 2: Savor the first sip.
Step 3: Let the whiskey rest in your mouth for a few seconds, allowing the flavors to dance on your palate.
Step 4: Gently swallow and let the magic unfold.
Step 5: Exhale and appreciate the lingering notes.
Step 6: Indulge in the explosion of flavors and enjoy every moment. 

You're very welcome for this whiskey-tasting wisdom! ☺️ 
Sláinte!

story time🕯️: I recently played in a scramble and I had quite the revelation. usually in scrambles my drives are always picked since I’m pretty accurate off the tee. but i got paired with players that were actually better than me and i was stoked for it thinking we can win

all day i was trying to bomb my driver so i can get my 2 drives in (we all know this feeling) and it was at that time my competitive spirit came out to play.

(my revelation is coming, I promise)

as I was swinging as hard as possible on my drives, after 12 holes i noticed i haven’t missed a fairway and i was hitting it further than i usually do. i’m not the type of player that usually focusses on distance because i know my strength is accuracy but i had this moment on the course where it all clicked, i can have both 😂 

this was a fun moment i wanted to share. scrambles are fun 

#golfstory #golfscramble #golfgame #golfcompetition #golfswing

〰️explore the surrounding areas of the Kawaguchiko lake
〰️catch a sunrise 🌄 
〰️plan a sunset over overlooking fuji
〰️dip in the onsen 
〰️roam off the beaten path

here are some of the fun things I learned about golfing in Japan so far ⛳️🇯🇵 

1. it feels illegal to hit a bonsai tree on the course
2. golf carts drive themselves 
3. golf carts fit the whole group + bags 
4. courses have 2 greens per hole (alternate 4 szns)
5. you get a nice lunch break between nines 
6. you’ll be given a locker/key to store belongings
7. you pay after you play
8. post-golf onsen is a thing that should be adopted everywhere 🧖🏻‍♀️

📍 Asagiri Jamboree Golf Club, JP
